erence and discontinuity in game history. From the domestication of vector graphics in the early years of videogame consoles to the proliferation of videogame piracy in South Korea in the 1980s, this book explores case studies that challenge taken-for-granted approaches to videogames, platforms, and their histories.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Jun 2021) 4aFilm, Media and Communication. 4aGame Studies. 4aMedia Studies. 4aNew Media and Technology. 7aART / Video Game Art.2bisacsh  aVideogame history, media archaeology, platform studies, media theory.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311066152108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishz978311061076508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Engineering, Computer Sciences 2019 Englishz978311061015408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Engineering, Computer Sciences 2019z9783110606096oZDB-23-DEI40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9789048540303zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789048540303423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9789048540303.jpg  a978-3-11-061015-4  EBOOK PACKAGE Engineering, Computer Sciences 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-061076-5  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-066152-1  Amsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2019b2019  aEBA_CL_MUAR  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_MUAR  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DEIb2019  aZDB-23-DGGb2019